🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ TCP 3-Way Handshake (🔥 VERY IMPORTANT)
Simple Idea

Before sending data, TCP establishes a connection using 3 steps.

Mental Model (Starting a Call 📞)

You: “Hello?”

Friend: “Yes, I hear you”

You: “Great, let’s talk”

Connection established ✅

Actual Steps

1️⃣ SYN → Client says “I want to connect”
2️⃣ SYN-ACK → Server says “Okay, I accept”
3️⃣ ACK → Client confirms

Connection starts.

Why It Works

Ensures:

both sides are ready

reliable communication

Memory Trick 🧠

SYN → SYN-ACK → ACK

Think: Request → Accept → Confirm

2️⃣ Error Detection (How Errors Are Found)
Simple Idea

Checks if data is corrupted during transmission.

Mental Model (Sending Exam Paper 📄)

If some pages are missing or changed → you verify.

Techniques

Parity bit

Checksum

CRC (Cyclic Redundancy Check)

Example

Sender sends:

1010101

Receiver checks correctness using rules.

Why It Works

Network noise can corrupt data → error detection ensures correctness.

Memory Trick

Error Detection = Data checking system

3️⃣ Switching Techniques (Deep Understanding)
Types

Circuit Switching

Packet Switching

Message Switching

Mental Model

📞 Circuit → Fixed road
📦 Packet → Split into pieces
📨 Message → Whole message at once

Key Idea

Internet uses packet switching because:

✔ efficient
✔ scalable
✔ flexible

Why It Works

Dynamic routing allows better performance.

Memory Trick

Packet = best for modern internet

